---
// One idea: I'd rather show you the revising than hand you a lacquered thing —
// a living line you can return to and find changed beats a sealed one that can't move.
---
<svg width="560" height="200" viewBox="0 0 560 200" role="img" aria-labelledby="rev-t">
  <title id="rev-t">On the left, a lacquered sealed block — smooth, closed, finished, and inert. On the right, a living line drawn, half-erased, redrawn, still open at its end, marked "still moving."</title>
  <!-- the lacquered block: sealed, finished -->
  <rect x="50" y="66" width="130" height="72" rx="4" class="ink block" fill="var(--paper-deep)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M62 78 C 100 72, 140 84, 172 76" opacity="0.5" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="58" y="160" font-size="14" opacity="0.7">lacquered — cannot move</text>
  <!-- the living, revised line -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M300 100 C 330 84, 360 116, 388 96" opacity="0.4" stroke-dasharray="2 4" />
  <path class="ink spine" d="M300 108 C 332 92, 356 124, 392 104 C 428 86, 452 116, 486 100" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M472 92 C 482 98, 488 101, 494 103 C 488 106, 481 112, 476 118" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="330" y="150" font-size="14">still moving — come back and find it changed</text>
</svg>
